organic liquid phase is pumped to raw material recovery and refining processing areas.  AN prestripper columns are used to remove waste from the liquid phase.  Refined ADN is used onsite and shipped offsite.  The co-products of ADN production are ADN flasher tails (AFT), PN, and low boiler make.  All three can be burned on site while AFT and PN can be sold.  ADN gets converted to hexamethylenediamine (HMD) in a two-phase hydrogenation reaction.  Co-products of HMD production are amine heads and bis-hexamethyleneriamine (BHMT).  Both can be sold or burned on site.

Site Leadership is committed to the development, implementation, and continuous improvement of an effective Integrated Management System (IMS) for Environmental, Safety, Security, Health, and Quality (ESSH+Q). This commitment is evidenced by management through the following: 
	taking accountability for the effectiveness of the management system; 
	ensuring the Ascend Policy and IMS objectives are established and are compatible with the strategic direction of the company; 
	ensuring that the IMS requirements are fully integrated into the facilitys daily operations and business processes (through training, two-way employee communications, management review, and/or internal audits); 
	ensuring resources needed for the IMS are available; 
	promoting the use of the process approach and risk-based thinking; 
	communicating the importance of effective management and conformance to requirements; 
	ensuring, through ongoing monitoring and measurement, that the IMS achieves intended results; engaging, directing, and supporting personnel, through an open-door policy, to contribute to the effectiveness of the IMS; 
	supporting other relevant management roles to demonstrate their leadership as it applies to their areas of responsibility; and 
